<h2 id="College-Board-Standards">College Board Standards<a class="anchor-link" href="#College-Board-Standards"> </a></h2><ul>
<li><p>Skill 1.B: Determine code that would be used to complete code segments (ie For, While, Recursion)</p>
<ul>
<li>When extending the Fibo class you had to pick the specific segment of code that would have to be put in the for/while/recursive loop</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Skill 4.C: Determine if two or more code segments yield equivalent results (be sure to Discuss how you know results are the same)</p>
<ul>
<li>We determined that there were 4 different ways to produce the same fibonacci code, with either stream, or a for/while/recursive loop</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Skill 5.A: Describe the behavior of a given segment of program code (describe the difference in recursion versus for &amp; while loops, perhaps add timing to determine speed)</p>
<ul>
<li>The 4 different methods have 4 different speeds and efficiencies. </li>
<li>The recursion code segment iterates by running the function called "recursion", which called the setdata method, and then re-runs itself by calling itself, and reducing limit by 1 each time, until limit = 0.</li>
<li>The while loop does the same as the recursive loop, but instead of calling itself over and over again, the loop is built into the "while" statement, which loops while (limit-- &gt; 0), which reduces limit each time by 1.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
